GETKEYThis utility waits for a keypress, and return the value of the keystrokeas a return code.Example:-     unset exit                ; * Survive non-zero return codes in EXEC files     echo Enter option (A or B)     GETKEY     set char {status}     echo                      ; * Put cursor onto newline          if {char} == 65 ; echo Option 'A' selected     else if {char} == 66 ; echo Option 'B' selected     else                 ; echo invalid option     endCopyright by Peter Watson, December 1988.